              I've been playing around with GnuPG for email encryption over the last week or so and have found that the biggest barrier is the difficulty in setting it up for the average user, so this writeup is great.<br /><br />My next biggest question:  How do you your public key out there?  Currently I've uploaded it to a keyserver and have a link to it in my email signature.<br /><br />Is there a better way?

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
