          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              A few things are missing from this article.<br /><br />There is a public infrastructure of OpenPGP public key servers.<br />You can upload your public key there and you can fetch other people's public keys, making it easier to share.<br /><br />However, this does not fix the issue of trusting keys. Ie &quot;I have this public key that says Peter Bright, but does it really belong to Peter Bright?<br />PGP/GPG uses a web of trust model: if Alice sign's Bob's key and Bob sign's Claire's key, then Alice will trust Claire's key too.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
    </table>
    
