          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              <div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Something as easy to use as Facebook, that automatically shares everyone's public keys with all their friends and contacts, and automatically encrypts all communications</div><br /><br />The problem with anything that automatically shares/befriends/encrypts in this situation is that it might automatically or accidentally share your private key with people you don't want it to. I think that is the big issue. <br /><br />If your private key is in the cloud, you lose, so anything cloud/webmail style just plain doesn't work. You have to store your keys locally, or keep <span style="font-style: italic">them</span> encrypted, which starts to get back into 'lots of hassle' territory.<br /><br />That is the real problem that needs solving. Keeping your private key safe enough <span style="font-style: italic">and</span> accessible enough. After that, the rest is trivial.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
