          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              Having the messages themselves be encrypted is really the ***ONLY*** solution, for e-mail, even if you have your own personal e-mail server.<br /><br /><br />The SMTP protocol used between mail servers has no encryption support.  So any e-mail that goes outside whatever webmail service you use (meaning pretty much anything where the sender and receiver are not in the same domain) is subject to wholesale monitoring of the internet.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
